PRIVACY POLICY

Last Updated: June 2026

Human Saga ("the App") is developed and operated by TonyIsrael.

This Privacy Policy explains how information is handled when you use Human Saga.

Information We Collect

Human Saga does not require users to create an account.

Human Saga does not collect personal information such as:

- Names
- Email addresses
- Phone numbers
- Physical addresses
- Location data

Game Data

The App may save game progress and settings locally on your device. This information remains on your device and is not transmitted to our servers.

Advertising

Human Saga may display advertisements provided by third-party advertising partners. These advertising services may collect certain non-personal information automatically to provide and improve advertisements.

The information collected by advertising providers may include:

- Device information
- Advertising identifiers
- App usage information
- General diagnostic information

Please refer to the privacy policies of the advertising providers used by the App for more information about their data practices.

Children's Privacy

Human Saga does not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe that a child has provided personal information through the App, please contact us so that appropriate action can be taken.

Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect the App and its users. However, no method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure.

Third-Party Services

The App may use third-party services, including advertising providers, which may have their own privacy policies and terms.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the App or through updated policy documents.

